DAY 3
LINUX COMMANDS

Users & Permissions
1. create group
sudo groupadd GSPractice

2. check if grps are created
getent groups 
cat /etc/group

3. add user
sudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash prachiti

4. check if user is added
getent passwd
id user

5. set password for user
sudo passwd username

6. add user to group
sudo usermod -aG GSPractice Prachiti

7. check if user is added by 
groups username
getent group groupname

Processes & Logs
1. List processes owned by root
ps aux | grep "^root"

2. top -n 1 -b | head -20

3. sudo systemctl status servicename
sudo systemctl status ssh
sudo systemctl start ssh
sudo systemctl enable ssh
sudo systemctl disable ssh

4. journalctl -u ssh
sudo journalctl -u  ssh --since "1 hour ago"

5. sudo grep "Failed password" /var/log/auth.log | tail -5
